§n§2math.NT§r§r
§6§lIrrationality measure and lower bounds for pi(x)§r

§8§oDavid Burt
Sam Donow
Steven J. Miller
Matthew Schiffman§r

§72014§r

Comments: \u00a77\u00a7oVersion 4.0, 7 ps. E. Kowalski and T. Rivoal point out that the irrationality bound on zeta(2) uses the PNT to bound lcm(1,...,n). We explore this connectionin greater detail, and modify the irrationality bound proofs. We
can get arbitrarily close to x /log x infinitely often, and thus see that the true value of pi(x) is a natural boundary for these techniques\u00a7r
